<article>
  <h1>Engineering Courses</h1>
   <video src="engineer.mp4" controls>

   </video>
   <h2>B.Tech-Programmes:</h2>
   <p>B.Tech is the most preferring course by the students. B.Tech is for studing Engineering. There are many engineering courses based
     upon the interest of the students. Some of them are:
   </p>

   <dl>
     <dt>Computer Science Engineering(CSE)</dt>
     <dd>Database System , Intelligent System , Networking and Security , Software Engineering.</dd>
     <dt>Electrical and Communication Engineering(ECE)</dt>
     <dd>Communication Systems , Digital Signal Processing , Wireless Communication Systems , Embedded Systems , VLSI Design , Robotics and Automation.</dd>
     <dt>Electrical and Electronics Engineering(EEE)</dt>
     <dd>Power System , Control and Instrumentation , Power Electronics and Drives , Robotics and Automation.</dd>
     <dt>Mechanical Engineering(ME)</dt>
     <dd>Thermal Engineering , Design , Industrial Engineering , Manufacturing Engineering , CAD or CAM &amp; Mechatronics.</dd>
     <dt>Civil Engineering(CE)</dt>
     <dd>Structural Engineering , Transportational Engineering , Environmental Engineering.</dd>
     <dt>Information Technology(IT)</dt>
     <dd>Database System , Intelligent System , Networking and Security , Software Engineering.</dd>
     <dt>Biotechnology(BT)</dt>
     <dd>Biochemical and Bioprocessing Engineering , Bioinformatics and Computational Biology , Pharmaceutical Engineering.</dd>
   </dl>
   <p>Along with these some universities offer minor subjects to the students to gain inter-disciplinary knowledge, provide an opportunity to students to become entrepreneurs and leaders.</p>

